## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="2201f-117">ときに<xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A>返します、境界のことを確認してチェックを実行する必要があります、`pointer`パラメーターが`null`します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2201f-117">When <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> returns, you should perform bounds checking by verifying that the `pointer` parameter is `null`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2201f-118">ない場合`null`、呼び出す必要があります、<xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>制約された実行領 (域 CER) 内のメソッド。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2201f-118">If it is not `null`, you must call the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method in a constrained execution region (CER).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2201f-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> 呼び出し、<xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>メソッドと、ポインターを公開します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2201f-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> calls the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method and exposes the pointer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2201f-120">異なり、<xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A>メソッド、ポインターの現在の位置は変わりません。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2201f-120">Unlike the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A> method, it does not change the current position of the pointer.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2201f-121">次の例では、使用する方法、<xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A>メソッド。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2201f-121">The following example demonstrates how to use the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> method:</span></span>  
  
```  
byte* pointer = null;  
RuntimeHelpers.PrepareConstrainedRegions();  
try {  
    MySafeBuffer.AcquirePointer(ref pointer);  
    // Use pointer here, with your own bounds checking.  
    }  
finally {  
    if (pointer != null)  
        MySafeBuffer.ReleasePointer();  
    }  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2201f-122">キャストする場合`pointer`(これは、バイトへのポインター) としてさまざまな型 (T \*) へのポインター、ポインターのアライメントの問題があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2201f-122">If you cast `pointer` (which is a pointer to a byte) as a pointer to a different type (T\*), you may have pointer alignment issues.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2201f-123">すべての範囲をこのポインターにチェックのための責任を行う必要があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2201f-123">You must take responsibility for all bounds checking with this pointer.</span></span>

